<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../layouts/head', { title: title }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/static-pages.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../layouts/nav') %>

  <main class="static-page">
    <div class="static-wrap">
      <header class="static-hero">
        <h1>About helloRun</h1>
        <p>helloRun is a running event platform for people who want to move on their own schedule while staying connected to organized events, visible progress, and a community that keeps showing up.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="static-grid">
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>For Runners</h2>
          <p>Find virtual or on-site events, register online, submit proof of your run, track review status, and collect certificates when your result is approved.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>For Organizers</h2>
          <p>Create events, manage registrations, review payment and run proof, publish leaderboards, and keep participants informed from one workflow.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="static-card">
        <h2>Why helloRun exists</h2>
        <p>Running is personal, but progress is easier to sustain when it feels shared. helloRun gives runners a simple way to join challenges and record achievements, while giving organizers the structure they need to run credible events without messy manual tracking.</p>
        <p>Our goal is to make running events easier to join, easier to manage, and easier to trust.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="static-card">
        <h2>What the platform handles</h2>
        <ul class="static-check-list">
          <li><i data-lucide="search"></i><span>Event discovery for virtual, on-site, and hybrid runs.</span></li>
          <li><i data-lucide="clipboard-check"></i><span>Registration, waiver capture, and participant records.</span></li>
          <li><i data-lucide="receipt"></i><span>Payment proof submission and organizer/admin review.</span></li>
          <li><i data-lucide="timer"></i><span>Run proof submission with distance, time, date, location, and supporting evidence.</span></li>
          <li><i data-lucide="award"></i><span>Approved results, public leaderboard visibility, and certificate access.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="static-grid">
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Built around trust</h2>
          <p>Every important action has a clear status: pending, submitted, approved, rejected, or completed. Runners know what is happening, and organizers can review proof before results become public.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="static-card">
          <h2>Built for momentum</h2>
          <p>helloRun keeps the process lightweight so runners can focus on moving and organizers can focus on creating better events, not chasing forms and screenshots across different tools.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="static-card about-cta-card">
        <h2>Start with the next run</h2>
        <p>Browse open events, join a challenge, or create an organizer account if you want to host your own running event.</p>
        <div class="static-actions">
          <a href="/events" class="btn">Browse Events</a>
          <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-secondary">Create Account</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <p class="static-note">Need help? Visit <a href="/faq">FAQ</a> or <a href="/contact">contact support</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../layouts/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
  <script>if (window.lucide) lucide.createIcons();</script>
</body>
</html>
